            <span style="min-width: 28px; height: 28px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--green); color: white; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700;">✓</span>
            <div><strong style="color: var(--slate-800);">Release begins</strong><br><span style="color: var(--slate-500);">We keep you updated</span></div>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>

    <style>
      @media (max-width: 640px) {
        section div[style*="grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr"] {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr !important;
          gap: 32px !important;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </section>

  <!-- ABOUT PAWNEE COUNTY JAIL — unique local content -->
  <section style="padding: 48px 1.5rem; background: var(--slate-50);">
    <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px;">About Pawnee County Jail</h2>
      <div style="color: var(--slate-600); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.7;">
        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">Pawnee County Jail is located at 500 Harrison Street in the city of Pawnee, Oklahoma 74058. The facility is operated by the Pawnee County Sheriff's Office and serves as the central booking and detention facility for all of Pawnee County. The jail is housed within the Pawnee County Courthouse complex on Harrison Street, which also contains the Pawnee County District Court and the Sheriff's administrative offices.</p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">The city of Pawnee sits in a historically significant area of north-central Oklahoma. It is the capital of the Pawnee Nation and home to the Pawnee Bill Ranch, a well-known historic site. The jail is centrally located in downtown Pawnee on Harrison Street. If you are driving from Stillwater, the facility is easy to find: take SH-51 East, then turn north on SH-18 into Pawnee. Harrison Street runs through the center of town. The courthouse and jail complex is prominently located and has visitor parking available.</p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">Pawnee County Jail handles all bookings from law enforcement across the county, including arrests from Cleveland, Ralston, Jennings, and the surrounding rural areas. The jail can be reached at (918) 762-2565 for inmate information, bail amounts, and booking details. Their fax number is (918) 762-6407. Inmates can receive mail addressed to the jail at 500 Harrison Street, Pawnee, OK 74058 -- be sure to include the inmate's full name and ID number on all correspondence.</p>
      </div>

      <h3 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px;">Bail Process at Pawnee County Jail</h3>
      <p style="color: var(--slate-600); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 14px;">When someone is booked into Pawnee County Jail, bail is typically set according to a standard bond schedule for common charges. For more serious charges, a judge may need to set the bail amount during a bond hearing, which can delay the process. Using a bail bondsman like Angel Bail Bonds is the fastest way to secure a release. We handle the paperwork, coordinate with the jail staff, and post the bond so that your loved one can be released as soon as the facility processes the paperwork. From Stillwater, Pawnee is only about 45 minutes away, and we regularly post bonds at this facility. Call us at (405) 614-3000 anytime, day or night.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ — compact accordion -->
